In this paper, we attempt to reconstruct the mortality pattern of the population 
buried in S'Illot des Porros (Majorca), an Iron Age necropolis in the western 
Mediterranean, by means of paleodemographic analysis. The skeletal sample 
consists of 285 individuals, 93 subadults (under 20 years old) and 192 adults. 
The aim of this study is twofold: first, to identify and to evaluate the 
structural anomalies of the skeletal sample, and second, to obtain a possible 
and realistic description of the biological dynamics of this population, with 
special reference to its mortality pattern. The study uses current demographic 
